10#ifndef PC_USED_IDS_H_
11#define PC_USED_IDS_H_
12
13#include <set>
14#include <vector>
15
16#include "api/rtp_parameters.h"
17#include "media/base/codec.h"
18#include "rtc_base/checks.h"
19#include "rtc_base/logging.h"
20
21namespace cricket {
22template <typename IdStruct>
23class UsedIds {
24 public:
25 UsedIds(int min_allowed_id, int max_allowed_id)
26 : min_allowed_id_(min_allowed_id),
27 max_allowed_id_(max_allowed_id),
28 next_id_(max_allowed_id) {}
29 virtual ~UsedIds() {}
30
31 // Loops through all Id in |ids| and changes its id if it is
32 // already in use by another IdStruct. Call this methods with all Id
33 // in a session description to make sure no duplicate ids exists.
34 // Note that typename Id must be a type of IdStruct.
35 template <typename Id>
36 void FindAndSetIdUsed(std::vector<Id>* ids) {
37 for (const Id& id : *ids) {
38 FindAndSetIdUsed(&id);
39 }
40 }
41
42 // Finds and sets an unused id if the |idstruct| id is already in use.
43 void FindAndSetIdUsed(IdStruct* idstruct) {
44 const int original_id = idstruct->id;
45 int new_id = idstruct->id;
46
47 if (original_id > max_allowed_id_ || original_id < min_allowed_id_) {
48 // If the original id is not in range - this is an id that can't be
49 // dynamically changed.
50 return;
51 }
52
53 if (IsIdUsed(original_id)) {
54 new_id = FindUnusedId();
55 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Duplicate id found. Reassigning from "
56 << original_id << " to " << new_id;
57 idstruct->id = new_id;
58 }
59 SetIdUsed(new_id);
60 }
61
62 protected:
63 virtual bool IsIdUsed(int new_id) {
64 return id_set_.find(new_id) != id_set_.end();
65 }
66 const int min_allowed_id_;
67 const int max_allowed_id_;
68
69 private:
70 // Returns the first unused id in reverse order.
71 // This hopefully reduces the risk of more collisions. We want to change the
72 // default ids as little as possible. This function is virtual and can be
73 // overriden if the search for unused IDs should follow a specific pattern.
74 virtual int FindUnusedId() {
75 while (IsIdUsed(next_id_) && next_id_ >= min_allowed_id_) {
76 --next_id_;
77 }
78 RTC_DCHECK(next_id_ >= min_allowed_id_);
79 return next_id_;
80 }
81
82 void SetIdUsed(int new_id) {
83 RTC_DCHECK(new_id >= min_allowed_id_);
84 RTC_DCHECK(new_id <= max_allowed_id_);
85 RTC_DCHECK(!IsIdUsed(new_id));
86 id_set_.insert(new_id);
87 }
88 int next_id_;
89 std::set<int> id_set_;
90};
91
92// Helper class used for finding duplicate RTP payload types among audio, video
93// and data codecs. When bundle is used the payload types may not collide.
94class UsedPayloadTypes : public UsedIds<Codec> {
95 public:
96 UsedPayloadTypes()
97 : UsedIds<Codec>(kFirstDynamicPayloadTypeLowerRange,
98 kLastDynamicPayloadTypeUpperRange) {}
99
100 protected:
101 bool IsIdUsed(int new_id) override {
102 // Range marked for RTCP avoidance is "used".
103 if (new_id > kLastDynamicPayloadTypeLowerRange &&
104 new_id < kFirstDynamicPayloadTypeUpperRange)
105 return true;
106 return UsedIds<Codec>::IsIdUsed(new_id);
107 }
108
109 private:
110 static const int kFirstDynamicPayloadTypeLowerRange = 35;
111 static const int kLastDynamicPayloadTypeLowerRange = 65;
112
113 static const int kFirstDynamicPayloadTypeUpperRange = 96;
114 static const int kLastDynamicPayloadTypeUpperRange = 127;
115};
116
117// Helper class used for finding duplicate RTP Header extension ids among
118// audio and video extensions.
119class UsedRtpHeaderExtensionIds : public UsedIds<webrtc::RtpExtension> {
120 public:
121 enum class IdDomain {
122 // Only allocate IDs that fit in one-byte header extensions.
123 kOneByteOnly,
124 // Prefer to allocate one-byte header extension IDs, but overflow to
125 // two-byte if none are left.
126 kTwoByteAllowed,
127 };
128
129 explicit UsedRtpHeaderExtensionIds(IdDomain id_domain)
130 : UsedIds<webrtc::RtpExtension>(
131 webrtc::RtpExtension::kMinId,
132 id_domain == IdDomain::kTwoByteAllowed
133 ? webrtc::RtpExtension::kMaxId
134 : webrtc::RtpExtension::kOneByteHeaderExtensionMaxId),
135 id_domain_(id_domain),
136 next_extension_id_(webrtc::RtpExtension::kOneByteHeaderExtensionMaxId) {
137 }
138
139 private:
140 // Returns the first unused id in reverse order from the max id of one byte
141 // header extensions. This hopefully reduce the risk of more collisions. We
142 // want to change the default ids as little as possible. If no unused id is
143 // found and two byte header extensions are enabled (i.e.,
144 // |extmap_allow_mixed_| is true), search for unused ids from 15 to 255.
145 int FindUnusedId() override {
146 if (next_extension_id_ <=
147 webrtc::RtpExtension::kOneByteHeaderExtensionMaxId) {
148 // First search in reverse order from the max id of one byte header
149 // extensions.
150 while (IsIdUsed(next_extension_id_) &&
151 next_extension_id_ >= min_allowed_id_) {
152 --next_extension_id_;
153 }
154 }
155
156 if (id_domain_ == IdDomain::kTwoByteAllowed) {
157 if (next_extension_id_ < min_allowed_id_) {
158 // We have searched among all one-byte IDs without finding an unused ID,
159 // continue at the first two-byte ID.
160 next_extension_id_ =
161 webrtc::RtpExtension::kOneByteHeaderExtensionMaxId + 1;
162 }
163
164 if (next_extension_id_ >
165 webrtc::RtpExtension::kOneByteHeaderExtensionMaxId) {
166 while (IsIdUsed(next_extension_id_) &&
167 next_extension_id_ <= max_allowed_id_) {
168 ++next_extension_id_;
169 }
170 }
171 }
172 RTC_DCHECK(next_extension_id_ >= min_allowed_id_);
173 RTC_DCHECK(next_extension_id_ <= max_allowed_id_);
174 return next_extension_id_;
175 }
176
177 const IdDomain id_domain_;
178 int next_extension_id_;
179};
180
181} // namespace cricket
182
183#endif // PC_USED_IDS_H_
